      <blockquote> 
        <h2 align="left">Set Simulation Layout</font></h2>
        <p align="left">Mike H. moves to the step of setting the layout for his 
          simulation on the set layout page (shown below). These layouts give 
          one an idea of what the final simulation will look like to the players.</p>
      </blockquote>
      <ul>
        <li>Currently one can pick between a horizontal layout (with all of the 
          'sections' the player can access listed across the top) or a vertical 
          layout (with all of the 'sections' that the player can access listed 
          down the left hand side.</li>
        <li>Jargon Alert: A 'section' can be thought of as a tab heading that 
          leads to a specific page where the player can see or do something.</li>
        <li>Right now the ability to customize the looks of a simulation is pretty 
          rudimentary. This step in the wizard will undoubtably be expanded greatly 
          in functionality.</li>
      </ul>
